definitions.definition: A goddess of fertility , love , sex , and war . In the Babylonian pantheon, she was the divine personification of the planet Venus; the Assyrian and Babylonian counterpart to the Sumerian Inanna and to the northwest-Semitic goddess Astarte .

main_definition: ( Mesopotamian mythology ) A goddess of fertility , love , sex , and war . In the Babylonian pantheon, she was the divine personification of the planet Venus; the Assyrian and Babylonian counterpart to the Sumerian Inanna and to the northwest-Semitic goddess Astarte .
